        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1960-09-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1960-09-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="298"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d298">
                <head>298. Memorandum of Discussion at the 461st Meeting of the National Security
                        Council<note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d298fn0">Source: Eisenhower
                        Library, Whitman File, <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Records. Top
                        Secret; Eyes Only. Prepared by <persName corresp="#p_BMW1"
                        >Boggs</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1960-09-29">September 29, 1960</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>[Here follow a paragraph listing the participants at the meeting and agenda items
                    1–2.]</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="italic">3. U.S. Policy Toward Greece</hi> (<gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                        >NSC</gloss> 5718/1; <gloss target="#t_OCB1">OCB</gloss> Report on <gloss
                        target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5718/1, dated September 14, I960)<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d298fn1">
                        <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5718/1 is printed in <ref
                            target="frus1955-57v24#pg_585">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1955–1957, vol. XXIV, pp.
                            585</ref>–<ref target="frus1955-57v24#pg_592">592</ref>. The <gloss
                            target="#t_OCB1">OCB</gloss> report of September 14 is not printed.
                        (Department of State, <gloss target="#t_OCB1">OCB</gloss> Files: Lot 62
                            <gloss target="#t_D1">D</gloss> 430, Greece)</note>
                </p>
                <p>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HKG1">Harr</persName> summarized the referenced
                    Operations Coordinating Board report on the subject, calling attention to five
                    aspects of our policy toward Greece: Cyprus, Greco-Soviet relations, the
                    economic situation in Greece, Greco-Turkish relations, and U.S. economic and
                    military assistance programs for Greece. Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HKG1"
                        >Harr</persName> said many portions of the policy <pb facs="0759" n="727"
                        xml:id="pg_727"/> paper were considerably out of date. However, the <gloss
                        target="#t_OCB1">OCB</gloss> had recommended a review of the policy rather
                    than a mere updating. Mr. <persName corresp="#p_GG1">Gray</persName> said the
                    Planning Board would proceed with a review of <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                        >NSC</gloss> 5718/1.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">The National Security Council:</hi>
                    <list>
                        <label>a.</label>
                        <item>Discussed the reference Report on the subject by the Operations
                            Coordinating Board, as summarized orally at the meeting by the Special
                            Assistant to the President for Security Operations Coordination.</item>
                        <label>b.</label>
                        <item>Noted that the <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Planning Board
                            would review U.S. Policy Toward Greece (<gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                                >NSC</gloss> 5718/1) as recommended by the Operations Coordinating
                            Board.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>[Have follow the remaining agenda items.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BMW1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Marion W. Boggs</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
